 {"id":"bd-rale","title":"Improve FfsError::Io errno mapping with ErrorKind fallback","description":"When std::io::Error has no raw_os_error() (e.g. created via Error::new()), to_errno() falls back to EIO. Improve by mapping io::ErrorKind to appropriate errnos (NotFound→ENOENT, PermissionDenied→EACCES, etc.) before falling back to EIO. This gives FUSE callers more specific error codes.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-26T00:49:02.204994325Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-26T00:59:08.073573327Z","closed_at":"2026-02-26T00:59:08.073546988Z","close_reason":"Improved to_errno() Io variant: now maps ErrorKind to specific errnos (NotFound→ENOENT, PermissionDenied→EACCES, AlreadyExists→EEXIST, WouldBlock→EAGAIN, InvalidInput/InvalidData→EINVAL, TimedOut→ETIMEDOUT, Interrupted→EINTR) when raw_os_error() is None, instead of always falling back to EIO. Added test io_error_kind_mapping_without_raw_errno covering all mapped kinds. Also fixed two pre-existing clippy pedantic lints. All 20 tests pass, clippy clean.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-rbm7","title":"Investigate failing btrfs FUSE E2E tests in workspace gate pass","description":"rch exec -- cargo test --workspace on 2026-04-07 surfaced a failure cluster in crates/ffs-harness/tests/fuse_e2e.rs. The failing cases were btrfs-focused FUSE E2E flows such as create, write, rename, xattr, setattr, fsync, and statfs, while the ext4/general FUSE tests in the same suite continued to pass. Goal: isolate the shared failure path, fix the root cause, and restore the targeted btrfs FUSE E2E contract.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-07T20:18:17.351947065Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-07T20:32:05.028230921Z","closed_at":"2026-04-07T20:32:05.027891889Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-rcumet","title":"Saturate MVCC RCU update counters","description":"`RcuCell` and `RcuMap` use wrapping atomic `fetch_add` for update counters. Long-lived metadata caches can wrap update_count back to zero, making debug output/churn telemetry misleading; `RcuMap::with_churn_threshold(0)` also leaves a modulo-by-zero panic path. Add saturating counter updates and threshold sanitization with focused regressions.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cod-fs","created_at":"2026-04-27T09:54:24Z","created_by":"cod-fs","updated_at":"2026-04-27T09:58:59Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T09:58:59Z","close_reason":"Routed RcuCell and RcuMap update counters through a saturating atomic helper, guarded zero churn thresholds from modulo-by-zero, and added numeric-limit plus zero-threshold regressions. Validation passed: RCU test subset, focused zero-threshold regression, fmt, diff-check, UBS touched file, workspace check, and workspace clippy.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
